2500|$|U.S. investors {{considering}} {{entering into}} a [...] "short against the box" [...] transaction {{should be aware}} of the tax consequences of this transaction. [...] Unless certain conditions are met, the IRS deems a [...] "short against the box" [...] position to be a [...] "constructive sale" [...] of the <b>long</b> <b>position,</b> which is a taxable event. [...] These conditions include a requirement that the short position be closed out within 30 days of the end of the year and that the investor must hold their <b>long</b> <b>position,</b> without entering into any hedging strategies, for a minimum of 60 days after the short position has been closed.|$|E
